	  <td>What interpreted text <em>means</em> is domain dependent. See
	    below.
d68 38
a105 3
	  <td nowrap><samp>\*escape*&nbsp;\`with`&nbsp;"\\"</samp>
	  <td>*escape* `with` "\"
	  <td>Escaped space ("<samp>\&nbsp;</samp>") may, in future, mean non-breaking space.
d108 8
d133 1
a133 1
      <li>An unescaped backslash preceding a start-string or end-string will
d138 29
a166 3
    <p>Also remember that inline markup may not be nested (well, except that
      inline literals can contain any of the other forms of markup, but that
      doesn't really count).
d171 1
a171 1
      <br>The simplest way to do this is to use raw strings:
d175 1
