	    <tr><td><strong>Dedication:</strong><td>To my father.
	  </table>
a545 2


d557 3
a559 3
      <tr valign="top">
	<td>
	  <pre>
d590 6
a595 6
	  </pre>
	<td>
Literal blocks are preceded by a
paragraph ending in two colons,
which is <em>shown</em> as just one in
the output:
d597 1
a597 1
<pre>
d603 1
a603 1
</pre>
d605 2
a606 2
<p>A space before the <samp>::</samp> causes it to
be omitted, like this
d608 1
a608 1
<pre>
d611 1
a611 1
</pre>
d613 1
a613 1
<pre>
d615 1
a615 1
</pre>
d617 3
a619 3
<p>They end when something returns to the
preceding paragraph's indentation. This
means that something like:
d621 1
a621 1
<pre>
d625 1
a625 1
</pre>
d627 1
a627 1
<p>is possible.
d641 2
a642 2
      <tr valign="top">
	<td><pre>
d648 3
a650 5
    </pre>
	<td>
	  Block quotes are just:
	  <blockquote>
	    <p>Indented paragraphs,
d652 4
a655 1
	      <p>and they may nest.
a656 1
	  </blockquote>
d666 7
a672 7
	  <tr align="left">
	    <th width="50%">Plain text
	    <th width="50%">Typical result
	</thead>
	<tbody>
      <tr valign="top">
	<td><pre>
d684 26
a709 26
	  </pre>
	<td>
	  <table align="center" border="1">
	    <tr valign="top">
	      <th>Header 1
	      <th>Header 2
	      <th>Header 3
	    <tr>
	      <td>body row 1
	      <td>column 2
	      <td>column 3
	    <tr>
	      <td>body row 2
	      <td colspan="2">Cells may span columns.
	    <tr valign="top">
	      <td>body row 3
	      <td rowspan="2">Cells may<br>span rows.
	      <td rowspan="2">
		<ul>
		  <li>Cells
		  <li>contain
		  <li>blocks.
		</ul>
	    <tr valign="top">
	      <td>body row 4
	  </table>
